{
  "_comment": "Plugin hook configuration. Loaded automatically when this plugin is enabled. Uses ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} placeholder so hooks resolve correctly regardless of where the plugin is installed.",
  "hooks": {
    "SessionStart": [
      {
        "matcher": "*",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/lifecycle/session-reset.js",
            "timeout": 3
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "UserPromptSubmit": [
      {
        "matcher": "*",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/lifecycle/prompt-enrich-trigger.js",
            "timeout": 3
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PreToolUse": [
      {
        "_comment": "GAP-G (v2.5.1): headless EnterPlanMode redirect. Detects `claude -p`/`--print` via parent-process command-line + permission_mode envelope field; denies EnterPlanMode in headless mode with forcing instruction redirecting to TodoWrite. Closes scenario-04 silent-failure where ExitPlanMode hung on the approval dialog and terminated the session before edits executed.",
        "matcher": "EnterPlanMode",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/pre/redirect-plan-mode-in-headless.js",
            "timeout": 3
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "ExitPlanMode",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/pre/verify-plan-gate.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_comment": "pre-spawn-tool-mask UNREGISTERED per ADR-0012: empirical probes proved a PreToolUse hook's updatedInput is INERT for Agent/Task spawns (the Agent tool_input has no `tools` field; updatedInput tool/prompt rewrites are not honored). Its network-strip never took effect. Capability enforcement is STATIC — the agent.md frontmatter tools: definition (harness-honored) + the agent.md<->contract reconciliation validator (contracts-validate.js). Network-axis binding in that validator is the follow-up.",
        "matcher": "Agent|Task",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/pre/route-decide-on-agent-spawn.js",
            "timeout": 6
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Agent|Task",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/pre/contract-reminder-on-agent-spawn.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Read|Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/pre/fact-force-gate.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/pre/config-guard.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_comment": "H.9.11: ordered FIRST among content-validators (after config-guard security gate); structural-before-semantic ordering. validate-yaml-frontmatter detects duplicate top-level YAML keys at Edit/Write time on HT-state.md; closes drift-note 80 URGENT 5-recurrence escalation.",
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/validators/validate-yaml-frontmatter.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/validators/validate-no-bare-secrets.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/validators/validate-frontmatter-on-skills.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/validators/validate-adr-drift.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/validators/validate-kb-doc.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_comment": "v2.9.0 FIX-I9: PreToolUse:Bash observability gate. Detects Bash redirects (>, >>, tee) targeting config-guard-protected files. WARN-not-BLOCK by default (architect.theo HIGH-5: avoid false-positive cliff). STRICT_CONFIG_GUARD=1 env var escalates to block. See kb:design-pushback/syntactic-gate-extension-for-tool-bypass for the design rationale.",
        "matcher": "Bash",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/validators/validate-config-redirect.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Bash",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/post/error-critic.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Agent|Task",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/post/kb-citation-gate.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_comment": "v3.0 Phase 1 prototype (P-Proto). Captures an L_spawn record envelope to ~/.claude/spawn-state/<run_id>/spawn-<id>.json on every Agent|Task spawn close. Empirical anchor for RFC v3.2-LOCKED's parent-records design (§Pivot 1 + §L_spawn record). Phase 1 scope: axioms + bounded sample fingerprint only; delta capture and parent_state_id chain deferred. Fail-soft per ADR-0001.",
        "matcher": "Agent|Task",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/spawn-state/spawn-record.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "Edit|Write",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/validators/validate-plan-schema.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "PreCompact": [
      {
        "matcher": "*",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/lifecycle/pre-compact-save.js",
            "timeout": 10
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "Stop": [
      {
        "matcher": "*",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/lifecycle/console-log-check.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "*",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/lifecycle/auto-store-enrichment.js",
            "timeout": 10
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "matcher": "*",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/lifecycle/session-end-nudge.js",
            "timeout": 3
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_comment": "GAP-F (v2.5.0): deterministic context-size warning. Inserted LAST in Stop chain so its forcing instruction is the final concatenation when multiple Stop hooks emit. Uses transcript_path bytes as the primary signal (ground-truth); falls back to turn counter if transcript_path missing.",
        "matcher": "*",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/packages/kernel/hooks/lifecycle/context-size-warn-stop.js",
            "timeout": 5
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
